WEBVTT

00:00:00.320 --> 00:01:45.400

00:01:57.920 --> 00:02:02.240
{\an8}If I didn't know you, I would've thought
you three were a family.

00:02:02.320 --> 00:02:05.080
{\an8}Here's to that douchebag
we have to forget.

00:02:05.840 --> 00:02:07.040
{\an8}He's worth nothing.

00:02:10.800 --> 00:02:12.280
{\an8}Wha-- Hey!

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:16.360
{\an8}Thirty-thousand?!

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:21.320
{\an8}I wonder who I threw up on.

00:02:24.360 --> 00:02:25.720
{\an8}Don't worry.

00:02:25.800 --> 00:02:29.760
{\an8}Once you get married,
maybe things will be better.

00:02:30.360 --> 00:02:34.560
{\an8}These days, there shouldn't be any
cliché mothers-in-law like in TV soaps.

00:04:24.520 --> 00:04:25.960
How could this happen?!

00:04:26.920 --> 00:04:30.120
I don't know how it tore either, Ma.

00:04:30.200 --> 00:04:32.240
It was already torn
before I got to iron it.

00:04:32.320 --> 00:04:33.760
How could you not know?!

00:04:33.840 --> 00:04:35.400
This is my favorite shirt!

00:04:35.480 --> 00:04:36.920
Do you know how much it cost?!

00:04:37.920 --> 00:04:40.200
If you fail this horribly
with some simple chores,

00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:42.240
how can I trust you to do anything?

00:04:43.720 --> 00:04:46.080
Ma, calm down, okay?

00:04:46.160 --> 00:04:47.440
Don't get mad at her.

00:04:47.520 --> 00:04:48.920
She didn't mean it.

00:04:49.520 --> 00:04:51.800
How about I buy you a new one, Ma?

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:54.400
Can't you see, Kuk?

00:04:54.480 --> 00:04:56.200
It's exactly like the master predicted.

00:04:56.280 --> 00:04:59.240
Your wife's nothing but bad luck.

00:04:59.320 --> 00:05:01.120
Anything she does turns to disaster.

00:05:01.200 --> 00:05:04.640
She'll surely lead you to total ruin!

00:05:04.720 --> 00:05:06.200
Good God!

00:05:06.280 --> 00:05:08.320
Ma, wait! Ma!

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:10.080
- Mook!
- Kuk…

00:05:11.440 --> 00:05:13.120
I swear I didn't do it.

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:15.840
It was torn before I even got to iron it!

00:05:19.120 --> 00:05:22.920
You know, if you didn't argue,
there wouldn't be a problem.

00:05:23.680 --> 00:05:25.240
You have to own up to what you do.

00:05:25.840 --> 00:05:27.200
Ma would've forgiven you.

00:05:29.360 --> 00:05:31.240
So you don't believe me either.

00:05:34.720 --> 00:05:36.640
I will prove it to your mother

00:05:36.720 --> 00:05:39.000
that I'm not bad luck,
like the fortune teller said.

00:05:39.640 --> 00:05:41.360
And I will bring you success

00:05:41.440 --> 00:05:43.880
better than your mother ever could!

00:05:43.960 --> 00:05:44.920
Just you wait.

00:06:38.200 --> 00:06:39.160
Have a seat.

00:07:01.200 --> 00:07:03.080
I called an urgent meeting today

00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:05.440
because I wanted to let you know

00:07:05.960 --> 00:07:09.480
we're trying to land a new client
who's a major account.

00:07:10.200 --> 00:07:13.880
Family Tour and Travel
can't fail on this one.

00:07:14.960 --> 00:07:17.080
But this time,
the client is hearing proposals

00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:19.440
from other agencies too,

00:07:19.520 --> 00:07:22.640
which means that we'll need to compete

00:07:22.720 --> 00:07:24.680
to win this project for our company.

00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:26.920
Who's our main rival, Ms. Usa?

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:28.920
Why does our president seem so tense?

00:07:30.960 --> 00:07:33.240
Our main rival is A Round Trip Travel.

00:07:38.520 --> 00:07:40.400
So we have to go against Ms. Mook?

00:07:40.480 --> 00:07:44.360
In that case, it's a tough spot
for our company.

00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:50.880
Let me know if any of you want out

00:07:50.960 --> 00:07:53.720
so I can find a backup team,

00:07:53.800 --> 00:07:56.080
because this is no place for losers.

00:07:57.280 --> 00:07:58.520
Especially

00:07:59.160 --> 00:08:01.400
those who lose
before even entering the field.

00:08:01.480 --> 00:08:03.200
That's not what we meant, Ms. Usa.

00:08:03.720 --> 00:08:07.680
We only meant that
since Ms. Mook knows how we operate,

00:08:07.760 --> 00:08:10.800
she might be able to predict our strategy.

00:08:10.880 --> 00:08:14.720
And that's exactly why we cannot lose.

00:08:26.720 --> 00:08:28.400
No way! Mook's going to quit?

00:08:28.480 --> 00:08:29.600
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:31.920
That's weird.

00:08:32.440 --> 00:08:34.960
The other day,
she was still giving us pep talks

00:08:35.039 --> 00:08:36.360
to boost our sales.

00:08:36.440 --> 00:08:37.799
It's true!

00:08:38.440 --> 00:08:40.120
I was about to go into the boss's office,

00:08:40.200 --> 00:08:44.360
and I heard them talking loud and clear.

00:08:45.920 --> 00:08:48.280
Then I'll quit to help our company.

00:08:49.080 --> 00:08:50.160
Please calm down, Mook.

00:08:51.120 --> 00:08:54.400
We'll surely fail without you this time.

00:08:55.720 --> 00:08:57.200
It really is strange.

00:08:57.720 --> 00:08:59.280
She's not here yet,

00:08:59.360 --> 00:09:01.840
but she's never late.

00:09:01.920 --> 00:09:04.160
Or maybe she had a fight with the boss.

00:09:04.240 --> 00:09:05.520
Or the boss had a fight with her.

00:09:05.600 --> 00:09:07.640
Or they're fighting over her commission.

00:09:07.720 --> 00:09:09.920
Or it's about the 30,000 baht in that note

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:11.520
- that someone sent her--
- Stop it.

00:09:11.600 --> 00:09:14.240
Stop guessing and just sit quietly.

00:09:15.120 --> 00:09:16.600
- But it's--
- Don't talk.

00:09:18.240 --> 00:09:19.920
Don't think. Don't guess.

00:09:25.600 --> 00:09:26.480
There's Mook!

00:10:06.360 --> 00:10:09.480
The meeting about our debut in Thailand
has been prepared, sir.

00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:12.960
Could you also arrange a date
for the travel agency briefing?

00:10:13.720 --> 00:10:17.520
I want an agency with a solid profile
to partner with our hotel.

00:10:17.600 --> 00:10:19.440
Once we opened the registration,

00:10:19.520 --> 00:10:23.480
we've received responses
from so many agencies.

00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:24.800
Here, sir.

00:10:29.440 --> 00:10:31.920
A laundry fee
has been transferred from Thailand.

00:10:32.520 --> 00:10:35.600
They sent an email
with an address for the receipt.

00:10:35.680 --> 00:10:38.040
Upon checking the address,

00:10:38.120 --> 00:10:42.160
I found that it matches
one of the agencies pitching for us.

00:10:42.800 --> 00:10:46.080
Here, sir. The agency's called
A Round Trip Travel.

00:10:47.320 --> 00:10:50.520
I've sent you money
for the priciest laundry fee on earth.

00:10:50.600 --> 00:10:53.800
I hope the actual receipt
matches the amount I sent you.

00:10:53.880 --> 00:10:55.400
Send it to this address,

00:10:55.480 --> 00:10:58.880
so I can be sure you aren't some scammer.

00:11:00.480 --> 00:11:03.400
I want to know everything
about A Round Trip Travel.

00:11:03.480 --> 00:11:04.480
In detail, please.

00:11:04.560 --> 00:11:05.720
Of course, sir.

00:11:40.880 --> 00:11:43.520
I looked into Narin Beach Resort
as you asked.

00:11:44.240 --> 00:11:46.920
It's a five-star beachfront hotel.

00:11:47.520 --> 00:11:49.080
There's only one major shareholder.

00:11:49.160 --> 00:11:50.240
A woman.

00:11:50.320 --> 00:11:53.160
She's around 50 years old, and she's Thai.

00:11:55.560 --> 00:11:58.600
That's her. Her name is Narin.

00:12:02.680 --> 00:12:03.520
Great work.

00:12:04.480 --> 00:12:08.120
Could you email me
the hotel's address and details?

00:12:08.200 --> 00:12:09.680
Of course, Mr. Thee.

00:12:12.360 --> 00:12:14.960
Remember, don't let anyone
know about this.

00:12:15.680 --> 00:12:16.720
Understood.

00:13:09.720 --> 00:13:11.320
VELUREE PINMOOK
ASSISTANT GUIDE

00:13:13.680 --> 00:13:18.760
The ordination hall's design reflects
the art style of the late Ayutthaya era,

00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:21.320
which was influenced by Chinese art.

00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:24.040
The style was the standard
during King Rama III's reign.

00:13:24.120 --> 00:13:26.080
Everyone, please take a look.

00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:28.960
These priceless murals,

00:13:29.040 --> 00:13:32.960
although faded with time,
remains as beautiful as ever.

00:13:38.200 --> 00:13:40.120
LUCKY GO TRAVEL

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:43.520
ONE THOUSAND BAHT

00:13:48.520 --> 00:13:49.920
We worked so hard,

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:52.040
yet this is all we got.

00:13:52.800 --> 00:13:55.080
I earn more from red envelopes, you know.

00:13:59.040 --> 00:14:02.040
Mook, should we ask my ma for help?

00:14:02.800 --> 00:14:04.520
She can pull some strings for us.

00:14:05.040 --> 00:14:07.280
My uncles own so many big companies.

00:14:07.880 --> 00:14:09.160
If we just ask Ma,

00:14:09.240 --> 00:14:11.080
we'll easily have a job in no time.

00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:13.600
We can even ask
for whatever salary we want, Mook.

00:14:15.320 --> 00:14:17.800
If you keep going to Ma for help,

00:14:17.880 --> 00:14:19.480
when will you grow up?

00:14:22.320 --> 00:14:24.480
You're the head of the family now.

00:14:24.560 --> 00:14:26.760
You need to learn
to stand on your own two feet.

00:14:28.840 --> 00:14:30.240
Just hold on a little longer.

00:14:30.320 --> 00:14:32.440
I promise we'll do better.

00:14:32.960 --> 00:14:33.800
You've got this!

00:14:37.800 --> 00:14:40.160
Come on. Hang in there, okay?

00:14:41.200 --> 00:14:42.160
Okay.

00:14:53.080 --> 00:14:54.880
This will really be our company?

00:14:54.960 --> 00:14:56.080
That's right, Kuk.

00:14:56.160 --> 00:14:58.800
We're about to own a small travel agency.

00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:00.480
Our own company.

00:15:00.560 --> 00:15:02.280
I promised you, remember?

00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:04.240
That our lives would get better.

00:15:07.800 --> 00:15:10.440
My wife really is the best!

00:15:11.800 --> 00:15:14.200
Kuk, what will we call it?

00:15:14.280 --> 00:15:17.240
Whatever you say, I'll agree with it.

00:15:17.320 --> 00:15:18.760
You want me to name it?

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:26.520
Then I'll name it…

00:15:27.520 --> 00:15:28.360
Family.

00:15:29.800 --> 00:15:32.080
How about Family Tour and Travel, Kuk?

00:15:32.160 --> 00:15:33.960
- Family Tour and Travel.
- Yeah.

00:15:34.720 --> 00:15:36.320
We're starting a small business.

00:15:36.400 --> 00:15:38.920
It's just like how
we're starting a family.

00:15:39.000 --> 00:15:42.920
We'll treat every client warmly,
as if they were family.

00:15:49.080 --> 00:15:52.560
But where will we get funding?

00:15:53.280 --> 00:15:56.080
In the beginning,
we'll need a lot of money.

00:15:59.360 --> 00:16:00.800
Should we ask Ma for help?

00:16:01.920 --> 00:16:03.680
I already applied for a loan.

00:16:05.720 --> 00:16:09.880
Kuk, we both need to work hard
so we can pay back the loan.

00:16:09.960 --> 00:16:13.280
I'm sure we can do it if we both try.

00:16:14.280 --> 00:16:15.320
We've got this.

00:16:21.880 --> 00:16:24.000
Then maybe your mother
will take me seriously.

00:16:25.040 --> 00:16:26.800
She'll see I'm not bad luck for you.

00:16:39.520 --> 00:16:42.600
Of course. Our company can handle any job.

00:16:44.080 --> 00:16:45.040
Really?!

00:16:46.200 --> 00:16:48.240
Thank you! I really appreciate it!

00:16:48.920 --> 00:16:50.120
Yes. Thank you.

00:16:51.240 --> 00:16:53.240
Kuk! Yay!

00:16:54.760 --> 00:16:56.000
We landed our first deal!

00:16:56.080 --> 00:16:57.600
It's a big tourist group from China.

00:16:57.680 --> 00:16:58.720
We did it, Kuk!

00:16:58.800 --> 00:17:00.400
Is that true, Mook?

00:17:03.120 --> 00:17:04.119
Hold on.

00:17:06.680 --> 00:17:08.160
Yes, Ma?

00:17:11.040 --> 00:17:11.920
What'd you say?

00:17:12.520 --> 00:17:13.839
Where are you?

00:17:14.599 --> 00:17:16.880
Got it. I'll be right over.

00:17:16.960 --> 00:17:18.240
Hang in there.

00:17:19.720 --> 00:17:22.440
Mook, Ma said she's sick.

00:17:22.520 --> 00:17:23.640
I'm going to see her.

00:17:24.240 --> 00:17:25.520
She's pretty close by.

00:17:26.200 --> 00:17:27.040
Uh… Kuk!

00:17:27.119 --> 00:17:28.240
- Kuk!
- Mook,

00:17:28.319 --> 00:17:30.720
a client's asking about a tour package.

00:17:30.800 --> 00:17:32.520
Okay, transfer the call to me.

00:17:36.320 --> 00:17:38.360
Hello, this is Mook speaking.

00:17:38.880 --> 00:17:42.160
Ma, you scared me!
I thought you weren't okay.

00:17:42.240 --> 00:17:44.160
What are you doing near my office?

00:17:44.920 --> 00:17:47.360
I wanted to have lunch
with you, of course.

00:17:47.440 --> 00:17:49.000
If I didn't lie,

00:17:49.080 --> 00:17:51.320
your wife wouldn't have let you come.

00:17:52.920 --> 00:17:54.120
Honestly, though,

00:17:54.200 --> 00:17:57.440
I just can't warm to her.

00:17:57.520 --> 00:18:00.080
She's so arrogant and stubborn.

00:18:01.440 --> 00:18:02.760
I'm in a good mood today,

00:18:02.840 --> 00:18:05.240
so please don't mention your wife.

00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:09.640
Mei,

00:18:10.360 --> 00:18:12.160
do you remember Kuk?

00:18:12.960 --> 00:18:15.800
When you were little,
you'd run and play together.

00:18:19.120 --> 00:18:20.320
Hello, Kuk.

00:18:21.360 --> 00:18:22.320
Hello.

00:18:22.400 --> 00:18:23.320
This is Mei.

00:18:23.400 --> 00:18:25.520
The daughter of Uncle Ko,
your pa's friend.

00:18:25.600 --> 00:18:26.960
Do you remember?

00:18:27.040 --> 00:18:29.880
When you were little,
she'd always visit us.

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:34.320
I remember now.

00:18:35.120 --> 00:18:36.520
You're scared of cats.

00:18:36.600 --> 00:18:39.040
You always came running to me
when you saw a cat.

00:18:39.640 --> 00:18:42.600
And are you still scared of them now?

00:18:42.680 --> 00:18:47.600
If you are,
you can always come to him, Mei.

00:18:48.680 --> 00:18:51.400
Ma! What are you saying?

00:18:51.480 --> 00:18:54.440
Don't be shy, now. Have a seat!

00:18:54.520 --> 00:18:56.560
Have a seat. You too.

00:18:56.640 --> 00:18:59.320
Why don't you two talk?
I'll be right back.

00:19:02.360 --> 00:19:03.720
So, are you still scared of cats?

00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:07.040
I still am.

00:19:10.120 --> 00:19:12.760
Thanks for hooking me up with that guide.

00:19:13.280 --> 00:19:14.680
No problem.

00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:16.240
When I saw your text,

00:19:16.320 --> 00:19:19.560
I remembered this guide
I kept seeing on my flights.

00:19:19.640 --> 00:19:21.400
He seems like a pro.

00:19:21.480 --> 00:19:23.520
His tourists seem to love him too.

00:19:26.520 --> 00:19:29.280
Mook, are you okay?

00:19:30.760 --> 00:19:33.800
You look so worn out
now that you're married.

00:19:33.880 --> 00:19:36.920
Marriage is nothing like in the novels.

00:19:37.680 --> 00:19:39.080
There's no romance.

00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:40.720
Only drama.

00:19:41.400 --> 00:19:43.440
Even some action sometimes.

00:19:45.080 --> 00:19:46.840
Doesn't Kuk help you at all?

00:19:47.720 --> 00:19:49.240
He does.

00:19:49.760 --> 00:19:51.720
But you know how he is.

00:19:53.760 --> 00:19:56.520
He can't keep being such a mama's boy.

00:19:56.600 --> 00:19:57.760
And where is he even?

00:19:57.840 --> 00:19:59.920
Why's he having you do all the work?

00:20:00.640 --> 00:20:03.600
His mother's sick today,
so he had to take care of her.

00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:08.240
I'm so hungry. Come on.

00:20:08.320 --> 00:20:09.800
My treat today.

00:20:09.880 --> 00:20:12.520
To thank my best friend
for hooking me up with that guide.

00:20:13.880 --> 00:20:17.080
There you go again,
defending him like always.

00:20:17.160 --> 00:20:18.960
Come on. What do you want to eat?

00:20:19.480 --> 00:20:21.560
Go all out. Limit's a hundred, though.

00:20:23.680 --> 00:20:25.600
- Where do we sit?
- I don't know.

00:20:30.560 --> 00:20:32.760
The dumplings here are so good.

00:20:32.840 --> 00:20:33.640
Enjoy, Mei.

00:20:34.680 --> 00:20:36.480
- Okay.
- Isn't that Kuk?

00:20:37.520 --> 00:20:39.280
But you said he's with his mother.

00:20:39.800 --> 00:20:42.880
- Is it good?
- Yes.

00:20:42.960 --> 00:20:45.960
So, what do you do?

00:20:46.040 --> 00:20:48.080
I just started a business.

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:49.400
So far so good.

00:20:52.560 --> 00:20:53.760
Mook.

00:20:53.840 --> 00:20:57.000
You told me your mother's sick,
so what are you doing here?

00:21:04.760 --> 00:21:07.920
Who are you? Don't you know he has a wife?

00:21:12.240 --> 00:21:14.800
So what if he does?

00:21:15.480 --> 00:21:16.440
Shameless bitch!

00:21:23.240 --> 00:21:24.080
Stop it!

00:21:24.160 --> 00:21:25.280
Hey!

00:21:25.360 --> 00:21:27.920
Mess with my friend
and I'll make sure you regret it!

00:21:30.240 --> 00:21:33.600
Who's this girl? Are you cheating on me?

00:21:35.920 --> 00:21:37.640
And why couldn't he?

00:21:42.880 --> 00:21:44.080
How embarrassing!

00:21:44.160 --> 00:21:46.400
Fighting at a restaurant like that.

00:21:46.480 --> 00:21:48.080
How thoughtless can you be?!

00:21:48.160 --> 00:21:50.240
I'm just so embarrassed.

00:21:52.600 --> 00:21:53.720
I'm sorry, Ma.

00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:58.400
But I really didn't expect you
to pull something like that.

00:21:58.480 --> 00:21:59.800
What are you trying to say?

00:22:01.160 --> 00:22:03.240
Why'd you lie about being sick?

00:22:03.840 --> 00:22:06.000
So that you could set up a date for him?

00:22:07.920 --> 00:22:08.920
She's right, Ma.

00:22:09.680 --> 00:22:12.520
Why'd you have to lie about being sick?

00:22:14.800 --> 00:22:16.440
Why else would I do it?!

00:22:16.520 --> 00:22:19.040
I was just going to ask Mei's dad, Ko,

00:22:19.120 --> 00:22:21.840
to book a tour with your company!

00:22:23.360 --> 00:22:24.920
I'm always misunderstood.

00:22:25.760 --> 00:22:26.920
Of course!

00:22:27.000 --> 00:22:31.280
Ever since you got married,
your Ma's always been the bad guy.

00:22:34.320 --> 00:22:35.680
Ma…

00:22:36.400 --> 00:22:39.680
I'm sorry, Ma. Don't cry, okay?

00:22:41.520 --> 00:22:43.600
Mook, say sorry.

00:22:44.240 --> 00:22:45.640
She's just trying to help.

00:22:50.480 --> 00:22:52.840
- It's alright.
- Forget it, Kuk.

00:22:52.920 --> 00:22:55.640
Your wife never respected me anyway!

00:22:57.160 --> 00:23:00.040
I'm so stressed out now.

00:23:00.120 --> 00:23:03.160
How can I apologize to Ko

00:23:03.240 --> 00:23:05.440
after what you did to his daughter?

00:23:06.160 --> 00:23:07.320
Good God!

00:23:07.400 --> 00:23:09.640
- Ma.
- I want to just pass out.

00:23:09.720 --> 00:23:12.000
Ma! Calm down, Ma.

00:23:12.080 --> 00:23:13.360
Let me make you some tea.

00:23:13.440 --> 00:23:14.360
Wait a second, okay?

00:23:19.720 --> 00:23:21.080
Why'd you do all this?

00:23:21.600 --> 00:23:23.960
Just tell me what you really want.

00:23:32.840 --> 00:23:36.440
I just want to find a good woman
who's right for my son.

00:23:37.080 --> 00:23:39.280
Since Kuk married you,

00:23:39.360 --> 00:23:41.720
you've both had to work hard
as mere employees

00:23:41.800 --> 00:23:44.200
till your skin turns all dull and tan.

00:23:44.720 --> 00:23:47.480
A dragon belongs with a swan,

00:23:47.560 --> 00:23:49.680
not an earthworm like you.

00:23:50.360 --> 00:23:53.040
Ma, here's some hot tea.

00:23:53.120 --> 00:23:54.720
I really can't take this, Kuk.

00:23:54.800 --> 00:23:56.880
- Ma!
- I have such a bad headache.

00:23:57.520 --> 00:23:59.640
Would you take me to rest in my room?

00:23:59.720 --> 00:24:01.560
If I stay here,

00:24:01.640 --> 00:24:04.520
I'll get all this bad energy
from your wife.

00:24:04.600 --> 00:24:06.320
It's going to kill me.

00:24:06.400 --> 00:24:07.240
- Ma…
- Come on.

00:24:07.320 --> 00:24:09.320
- Let's go, honey.
- Careful, Ma.

00:24:09.400 --> 00:24:10.680
Careful.

00:24:18.000 --> 00:24:20.480
{\an8}Now where should I put this?

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:24.880
{\an8}The south for wealth and fame?

00:24:27.560 --> 00:24:28.600
{\an8}That won't do.

00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:31.160
Or the north?

00:24:31.240 --> 00:24:33.880
North is better.

00:24:33.960 --> 00:24:37.560
For a good career
and support from the higher-ups.

00:24:39.360 --> 00:24:40.840
Perfect!

00:24:41.640 --> 00:24:42.640
Too low…

00:25:20.800 --> 00:25:21.920
Ma, what are you doing?

00:25:23.760 --> 00:25:24.720
- Ma!
- Ma!

00:25:24.800 --> 00:25:27.640
Ma! Don't get up too quick.

00:25:28.160 --> 00:25:29.600
Easy.

00:25:32.640 --> 00:25:34.200
Are you okay?

00:25:41.960 --> 00:25:43.680
I'm so cursed.

00:25:43.760 --> 00:25:47.200
But I walked out the house
with my left foot first this morning!

00:25:47.280 --> 00:25:49.240
Maybe I just have bad luck today.

00:25:51.240 --> 00:25:52.880
Let me give you a massage, Ma.

00:25:53.840 --> 00:25:55.400
Thank you, dear.

00:25:55.920 --> 00:25:58.960
You're always so sweet, Usa.

00:25:59.960 --> 00:26:02.040
Ma, what's this?

00:26:02.120 --> 00:26:03.400
Why'd you bring a dog statue?

00:26:03.480 --> 00:26:06.480
A dog my ass! That's a dragon-- Oh no!

00:26:06.560 --> 00:26:08.000
{\an8}A beheaded dragon!

00:26:08.080 --> 00:26:09.600
That's a bad omen.

00:26:09.680 --> 00:26:11.600
We need to glue it back. Give it to me!

00:26:12.600 --> 00:26:14.160
Oh dear…

00:26:15.160 --> 00:26:17.280
Oh dear…

00:26:17.360 --> 00:26:20.560
I was trying to improve
the room's feng shui for you,

00:26:20.640 --> 00:26:22.600
so you'd have a good luck.

00:26:24.000 --> 00:26:25.280
He'll need it, Ma.

00:26:25.360 --> 00:26:29.000
Kuk's about to face a big battle,
going up against his ex-wife.

00:26:30.960 --> 00:26:34.120
What'd you just say? His ex-wife?

00:26:36.720 --> 00:26:38.360
I knew it.

00:26:38.440 --> 00:26:40.400
No wonder I'm so unlucky today.

00:26:40.480 --> 00:26:42.360
It's because I have
to face that damn girl.

00:26:42.880 --> 00:26:46.520
Whenever I see her, I'm always so unlucky.

00:26:53.480 --> 00:26:55.120
Ma, I'm home.

00:26:55.880 --> 00:26:58.280
It's good you're home. I've been hungry.

00:26:58.360 --> 00:27:00.640
But I'm having a run of good luck.

00:27:00.720 --> 00:27:02.240
I can't get up or it'll go away.

00:27:02.840 --> 00:27:03.680
Mook,

00:27:04.200 --> 00:27:06.160
can you make some food
for me and my friends?

00:27:06.240 --> 00:27:07.440
And be quick.

00:27:07.520 --> 00:27:11.000
Ma, it's late,
and I have to get up early tomorrow.

00:27:11.080 --> 00:27:12.800
How about I order some food for you?

00:27:12.880 --> 00:27:13.880
What would you like?

00:27:13.960 --> 00:27:15.480
No, no.

00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:17.280
I don't do junk food.

00:27:17.360 --> 00:27:18.560
Just cook. It'll be quick.

00:27:18.640 --> 00:27:20.040
And clean the kitchen too.

00:27:21.280 --> 00:27:23.000
What happened to your maid?

00:27:23.080 --> 00:27:25.400
She moved back home out of town.

00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:29.720
Hurry up and do it for me, would you?

00:27:30.960 --> 00:27:32.560
Come on. Let's continue.

00:27:32.640 --> 00:27:34.480
I'm on a roll now.

00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:36.360
- Are you folding?
- Please, Mook.

00:27:36.880 --> 00:27:38.880
Can you do this for her?

00:27:38.960 --> 00:27:40.880
She wants to taste the food you make.

00:27:42.280 --> 00:27:43.240
Please?

00:27:43.840 --> 00:27:45.080
I'll go shower upstairs.

00:28:01.560 --> 00:28:04.320
Ma, you have some guests.

00:28:04.400 --> 00:28:06.080
At this damn hour?

00:28:06.160 --> 00:28:07.480
They'll mess up my luck.

00:28:07.560 --> 00:28:08.920
Tell them to wait!

00:28:16.360 --> 00:28:18.840
Wha-- Where are you all going?

00:28:18.920 --> 00:28:20.760
Quitting 'cause you're losing? No way!

00:28:20.840 --> 00:28:23.240
Get back here and finish the round!

00:28:23.320 --> 00:28:25.320
I'm on a roll, you know.

00:28:25.400 --> 00:28:28.760
Ma, don't keep your guests waiting.

00:28:44.040 --> 00:28:45.240
Please come with us.

00:28:46.600 --> 00:28:48.120
I'm just drinking tea.

00:28:52.160 --> 00:28:53.680
Please come with me to the station.

00:28:53.760 --> 00:28:55.800
I can't. I can't go anywhere.

00:28:55.880 --> 00:28:56.920
I need to finish ironing.

00:29:02.440 --> 00:29:04.080
You'd never finish anyway, ma'am.

00:29:04.960 --> 00:29:05.920
Please.

00:29:10.400 --> 00:29:11.880
You did this, didn't you, Mook?

00:29:11.960 --> 00:29:15.320
You told me not to order food,
but you didn't tell me not to call them.

00:29:15.400 --> 00:29:16.600
Gambling's a small crime anyway.

00:29:16.680 --> 00:29:18.120
I'll bail you out, okay?

00:29:19.280 --> 00:29:21.840
- Let's go, ma'am.
- Kuk!

00:29:21.920 --> 00:29:23.920
Kuk, help me!

00:29:24.000 --> 00:29:26.800
Your wife called the cops on me! Kuk!

00:29:32.480 --> 00:29:34.800
So this is where she
and her new man works.

00:29:35.560 --> 00:29:36.480
Yes, Ma.

00:29:36.560 --> 00:29:39.480
The owner's called Anapat.

00:29:39.560 --> 00:29:42.600
I heard he's quite charming.

00:29:42.680 --> 00:29:44.400
That witch!

00:29:44.480 --> 00:29:46.240
Leaving her ex for a new husband,

00:29:46.320 --> 00:29:48.720
and they work at a rival company.

00:29:48.800 --> 00:29:50.960
I warned Kuk, but he wouldn't listen.

00:29:51.040 --> 00:29:53.680
This girl is a curse!

00:29:54.200 --> 00:29:56.080
- Let's go!
- Where are we going, Ma?

00:29:56.160 --> 00:29:57.920
To teach her a lesson,

00:29:58.000 --> 00:30:01.120
so she'd know better
than to steal Kuk's job!

00:30:01.960 --> 00:30:03.320
Then we'll see,

00:30:03.400 --> 00:30:05.520
between her and Madam Tiansee,

00:30:05.600 --> 00:30:07.000
who comes out on top!

00:30:13.480 --> 00:30:14.760
Sis!

00:30:16.040 --> 00:30:17.640
{\an8}- You…
- What is it? I'm in a hurry.

00:30:17.720 --> 00:30:19.760
Mook, are you, you know,

00:30:19.840 --> 00:30:21.920
- quitting--
- Mook!

00:30:26.400 --> 00:30:28.560
I heard you got a new husband?

00:30:29.200 --> 00:30:32.640
How nice. Didn't take you long
to find a new pole to cling on to.

00:30:34.040 --> 00:30:35.520
Anything urgent?

00:30:35.600 --> 00:30:37.080
What brings you both here?

00:30:37.160 --> 00:30:41.040
I just wanted to see if you found
a better husband than my son.

00:30:42.200 --> 00:30:43.120
Let's see…

00:30:45.560 --> 00:30:47.080
Not bad!

00:30:47.960 --> 00:30:51.200
How nice. Relying only on rich guys.

00:30:51.280 --> 00:30:52.200
Auntie!

00:30:53.280 --> 00:30:54.120
Who are you?

00:30:54.920 --> 00:30:57.600
How could you stand there
and yell at someone like that?

00:30:58.200 --> 00:31:01.600
If you want to know,
why don't you ask Mook?

00:31:01.680 --> 00:31:04.280
See if she can remember
her previous mother-in-law.

00:31:04.360 --> 00:31:05.480
What?

00:31:10.600 --> 00:31:11.640
It's alright, May.

00:31:12.280 --> 00:31:13.760
You wouldn't understand her.

00:31:14.560 --> 00:31:16.440
She doesn't speak our language.

00:31:16.520 --> 00:31:17.840
Oh, yeah?

00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:20.480
Then what language
do I have to speak to this auntie?

00:31:21.200 --> 00:31:22.640
Try barking.

00:31:23.360 --> 00:31:24.800
But I don't know how to bark.

00:31:24.880 --> 00:31:26.280
That's why we could never talk.

00:31:26.360 --> 00:31:29.000
Mook! Are you calling me a dog?!

00:31:29.080 --> 00:31:29.920
Stop!

00:31:32.200 --> 00:31:34.600
If you don't, I'll call
the cops on you for trespassing.

00:31:34.680 --> 00:31:35.960
Ma…

00:31:39.480 --> 00:31:40.520
Who are you?

00:31:41.800 --> 00:31:44.360
Honey, you finally came.

00:31:46.760 --> 00:31:52.000
This auntie just wanted to see
if we're both happy and well.

00:31:55.240 --> 00:31:59.360
You see, Auntie, I'm doing so great.

00:31:59.880 --> 00:32:01.640
So don't worry about me.

00:32:01.720 --> 00:32:06.200
Why don't you spend that energy
on your son, who's still a manchild?

00:32:06.280 --> 00:32:07.160
Hey! Mook, you--!

00:32:11.280 --> 00:32:13.400
Please give that to your son.

00:32:14.240 --> 00:32:16.760
I don't need all that old, worthless junk.

00:32:16.840 --> 00:32:18.200
It's a waste of space.

00:32:18.280 --> 00:32:19.480
Is everything alright?

00:32:24.040 --> 00:32:25.400
Let's leave, Ma.

00:32:29.360 --> 00:32:31.240
This isn't over, Mook.

00:32:33.600 --> 00:32:38.880
And go tell your son
A Round Trip Travel will win this deal.

00:32:41.440 --> 00:32:42.320
Whatcha lookin' at?!

00:32:43.240 --> 00:32:44.160
Move!

00:32:49.240 --> 00:32:51.840
So, you've decided, Mook?

00:32:54.360 --> 00:32:57.720
Yes, Boss. We need to win on this one.

00:32:59.360 --> 00:33:02.280
Mook, you're not quitting anymore, right?

00:33:03.320 --> 00:33:04.800
Who said I'm quitting?

00:33:04.880 --> 00:33:06.360
I never even thought of that.

00:33:06.440 --> 00:33:07.280
What?

00:33:08.280 --> 00:33:09.560
Why'd you pack your things up?

00:33:11.280 --> 00:33:12.760
I just wanted to get rid of my old stuff.

00:33:12.840 --> 00:33:14.600
There's no use keeping it.

00:33:14.680 --> 00:33:18.360
Fierce and fabulous!

00:33:18.440 --> 00:33:21.240
- Glad you're staying!
- Come on.

00:33:21.320 --> 00:33:23.920
You were so savage! Slay!

00:33:27.200 --> 00:33:28.680
That Mook's really something, Kuk.

00:33:28.760 --> 00:33:30.960
I just meant to say hello,

00:33:31.040 --> 00:33:32.880
and she kept yelling at me,

00:33:32.960 --> 00:33:36.320
saying I raised you badly
and made you a manchild.

00:33:37.880 --> 00:33:40.000
I'm telling the truth, Kuk!

00:33:40.080 --> 00:33:41.760
Usa heard it all.

00:33:42.280 --> 00:33:45.560
And worst of all,
she has a new husband now!

00:33:46.160 --> 00:33:49.680
She was clutching his arms
like she's trying to possess him.

00:33:49.760 --> 00:33:52.120
Oh, and she even told me to tell you

00:33:52.200 --> 00:33:55.360
her new husband
is a thousand times better than you.

00:33:56.240 --> 00:33:57.720
And she even told me to tell you

00:33:57.800 --> 00:34:00.360
that her company's
winning the deal for sure!

00:34:02.520 --> 00:34:04.560
All this talking's making me lightheaded.

00:34:04.640 --> 00:34:06.320
Can you bring me my inhaler?

00:34:06.400 --> 00:34:08.480
- Where is it, Ma?
- In my purse.

00:34:09.440 --> 00:34:11.600
- Here you go. Inhale it.
- Yeah, that one.

00:34:11.679 --> 00:34:14.000
Relax and inhale.

00:34:14.800 --> 00:34:16.960
But what your mother said is true, Kuk.

00:34:17.040 --> 00:34:19.080
What Mook did was disgusting.

00:34:19.159 --> 00:34:21.880
She was being so rude
and disrespectful to Ma.

00:34:21.960 --> 00:34:24.199
And she chased us off like we're animals.

00:34:24.280 --> 00:34:27.719
If you'd seen it,
you surely couldn't stand it.

00:34:36.560 --> 00:34:38.400
We have to beat A Round Trip Travel.

00:34:39.920 --> 00:34:42.719
Good! You better show that Mook

00:34:42.800 --> 00:34:46.600
that she'll never win
against a dragon like you.

00:34:47.120 --> 00:34:49.199
Never!

00:34:53.360 --> 00:34:57.800
I'll show her that
leaving me was a mistake.

00:35:01.040 --> 00:35:03.800
Usa, prepare to attend the briefing.

00:35:18.080 --> 00:35:20.960
Mr. Thee, we're flying to Thailand
early tomorrow.

00:35:21.040 --> 00:35:23.520
I've already prepared
everything for you, sir.

00:35:23.600 --> 00:35:24.720
Thank you.

00:35:24.800 --> 00:35:26.440
How long are you staying in Thailand?

00:35:26.520 --> 00:35:27.960
I need to know so I can plan ahead.

00:35:38.080 --> 00:35:39.400
I'm not sure yet.

00:35:40.360 --> 00:35:43.160
This time, there'll be
many fun things to do.

00:35:45.480 --> 00:35:48.760
I've emailed you the information
on A Round Trip Travel, Mr. Thee.

00:35:50.280 --> 00:35:51.480
Okay.

00:35:52.000 --> 00:35:53.200
Alright.

00:36:11.000 --> 00:36:12.960
INFORMATION ON A ROUND TRIP TRAVEL

00:36:15.760 --> 00:36:17.360
INQUIRE OR BOOK A TOUR
VELUREE PINMOOK, MANAGER

00:36:20.520 --> 00:36:23.200
{\an8}Ma'am, you're in the wrong room.

00:36:33.440 --> 00:36:35.040
I did some research.

00:36:35.120 --> 00:36:38.040
TJ Group is a major real estate company

00:36:38.120 --> 00:36:42.080
that's partnered in megaprojects
with both the private and public sectors.

00:36:42.160 --> 00:36:46.080
They're looking to expand their business
to countries in Asia.

00:36:47.480 --> 00:36:49.280
Very thorough research, Whan.

00:36:57.920 --> 00:36:59.760
- Hey!
- What?

00:37:05.040 --> 00:37:07.040
I'm looking up the CEO
of the company, Boss.

00:37:08.960 --> 00:37:10.800
He's so hot!

00:37:10.880 --> 00:37:15.320
He even studied abroad and was awarded
the Young Rising Star CEO of the Year!

00:37:15.400 --> 00:37:17.760
Right. Very helpful information.

00:37:19.200 --> 00:37:21.040
What does this have to do with work?

00:37:22.680 --> 00:37:23.880
Of course it does.

00:37:23.960 --> 00:37:26.600
We need to look up everyone
we do business with,

00:37:26.680 --> 00:37:30.120
in case he comes to Thailand,
and we meet him, that way, we'll know…

00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:32.480
how to win his heart.

00:37:34.320 --> 00:37:36.200
That might be a little tough, May.

00:37:36.280 --> 00:37:38.360
Because from what I've read,

00:37:38.440 --> 00:37:42.000
he's very private, and he doesn't share
about his personal life much.

00:37:42.600 --> 00:37:44.280
Actually, he's not just

00:37:44.360 --> 00:37:46.680
the Young Rising Star CEO of the Year,

00:37:46.760 --> 00:37:51.160
but he was also the youngest person
to receive the Best CEO award.

00:37:51.240 --> 00:37:52.440
He really is something.

00:37:53.920 --> 00:37:54.920
Enough about him.

00:37:55.000 --> 00:37:58.040
Boss, tomorrow
there's a briefing at The One Hotel.

00:37:58.120 --> 00:37:59.000
Will you come with me?

00:38:00.200 --> 00:38:01.280
Sure.

00:38:01.360 --> 00:38:03.520
I've been wanting to meet this CEO.

00:38:04.040 --> 00:38:05.800
I heard all the companies will be there.

00:38:06.400 --> 00:38:07.440
Got it.

00:38:07.520 --> 00:38:09.680
That means you'll have to meet

00:38:10.280 --> 00:38:11.880
those Family Tour guys.

00:38:12.800 --> 00:38:15.040
I'm still in shock from earlier.

00:38:15.120 --> 00:38:16.920
That annoying old lady…

00:38:17.000 --> 00:38:19.160
Her scariness is a ten out of ten.

00:38:19.760 --> 00:38:22.440
Yeah, what we saw today was so scary.

00:38:22.520 --> 00:38:24.600
Even scarier than what I heard.

00:38:24.680 --> 00:38:26.120
How'd you stand her for so long?

00:38:31.640 --> 00:38:34.960
I'm Veluree. I never enter
a battle I'm not ready for.

00:38:35.840 --> 00:38:37.120
And once I decide to,

00:38:38.080 --> 00:38:39.480
I must never lose.

00:38:43.240 --> 00:38:44.200
It's time to unite!

00:38:50.400 --> 00:38:51.520
Boss?

00:38:52.480 --> 00:38:53.480
- Please.
- Come on, Boss.

00:38:53.560 --> 00:38:54.480
Me too?

00:38:58.400 --> 00:39:01.440
- A Round Trip Travel, let's go!
- A Round Trip Travel, let's go!

00:39:03.680 --> 00:39:04.880
‪Let's go!

00:39:04.960 --> 00:39:05.840
Right.

00:39:12.360 --> 00:39:13.640
You're way more handsome.

00:39:19.320 --> 00:39:21.800
That's enough, Ma! I can't breathe.

00:39:21.880 --> 00:39:23.360
I'll be dead before the briefing.

00:39:24.360 --> 00:39:25.760
Don't say that!

00:39:25.840 --> 00:39:28.400
Don't jinx it
on an auspicious day like this.

00:39:28.480 --> 00:39:31.400
We need to chase off all bad energy.

00:39:31.480 --> 00:39:32.880
Chase off our enemies.

00:39:32.960 --> 00:39:34.920
Chase off evil spirits.

00:39:35.000 --> 00:39:38.000
Oh, and your ex-wife too.

00:39:39.240 --> 00:39:43.960
I pray that victory may be yours only.

00:39:47.560 --> 00:39:48.400
That's enough.

00:39:48.480 --> 00:39:52.280
- Fire! Help! There's a fire!
- Huh? A fire?!

00:39:52.360 --> 00:39:54.520
- Fire! Help!
- Fire?!

00:39:54.600 --> 00:39:55.960
Where's the fire?

00:39:56.040 --> 00:39:57.560
Where?

00:39:57.640 --> 00:39:59.160
- Whe--
- Oh, so it's just incense.

00:39:59.240 --> 00:40:01.000
I thought there was a fire.

00:40:10.360 --> 00:40:11.240
Are you ready, honey?

00:40:11.840 --> 00:40:13.080
- Yes.
- Let's go.

00:40:16.040 --> 00:40:16.880
Ma, I'm leaving now.

00:40:16.960 --> 00:40:19.000
Wait, wait, wait!

00:40:19.080 --> 00:40:20.600
Come and fuel up first.

00:40:21.600 --> 00:40:23.880
Stick one in here.

00:40:28.600 --> 00:40:29.520
Chug it. Chug.

00:40:32.960 --> 00:40:35.480
Yeah, just like that.

00:40:38.640 --> 00:40:42.160
- Good luck, young man.
- Let's go.

00:40:57.800 --> 00:40:59.400
Why isn't Boss here yet?

00:41:07.280 --> 00:41:08.200
Where are you, Boss?

00:41:10.520 --> 00:41:11.440
What?

00:41:13.480 --> 00:41:15.760
Uh… Sure.

00:41:23.280 --> 00:41:24.600
Where are you going, Mr. Thee?

00:41:25.200 --> 00:41:26.280
I want to take a little walk.

00:41:26.360 --> 00:41:27.560
There's still time, right?

00:41:28.480 --> 00:41:30.280
Yes, sir. Should I come with you?

00:41:30.360 --> 00:41:31.520
It's fine.

00:41:32.200 --> 00:41:35.280
I just want to walk around
and see the hotel in case I get an idea.

00:41:38.960 --> 00:41:40.200
I can go alone.

00:41:41.440 --> 00:41:43.560
You should prepare
for the meeting, Mr. Pitak.

00:41:51.320 --> 00:41:52.320
Yes, Boss?

00:41:54.400 --> 00:41:55.640
I'm here now.

00:41:57.360 --> 00:41:58.400
Okay.

00:42:13.080 --> 00:42:15.400
It's my fault for not checking first.

00:42:16.240 --> 00:42:17.640
Can we still buy a new pair?

00:42:20.120 --> 00:42:21.360
Too late for that, Boss.

00:42:21.440 --> 00:42:23.360
It's almost time for the meeting.

00:42:33.600 --> 00:42:35.080
Take off your pants, please.

00:42:35.160 --> 00:42:36.000
What?

00:42:36.520 --> 00:42:37.840
Boss…

00:42:59.240 --> 00:43:01.200
- Mook.
- Yes.

00:43:01.960 --> 00:43:05.080
- Can I help you?
- Don't worry. Just stand still and relax.

00:43:08.320 --> 00:43:10.200
I'll finish in just a second.

00:43:12.000 --> 00:43:14.560
I do this all the time.
Just trust my hands, okay?

00:43:15.080 --> 00:43:16.000
Are you almost there?

00:43:17.480 --> 00:43:18.480
I'm almost there.

00:43:18.560 --> 00:43:19.640
Just a bit more.

00:43:28.480 --> 00:43:29.400
Are you okay?

00:43:34.960 --> 00:43:36.120
Just a little longer.

00:43:36.640 --> 00:43:37.480
I'm almost finished.

00:43:39.200 --> 00:43:40.040
I finished.

00:43:46.880 --> 00:43:47.800
Alright, Boss.

00:43:59.640 --> 00:44:01.320
- We should hurry.
- Yeah.

00:44:14.920 --> 00:44:16.040
So it's you again…

00:44:22.040 --> 00:44:22.960
Come on.

00:44:25.480 --> 00:44:26.360
You okay?

00:44:28.000 --> 00:44:29.120
Thank you, Mook.

00:44:29.640 --> 00:44:31.400
I would've been so embarrassed.

00:44:32.120 --> 00:44:33.680
It's nothing, Boss.

00:44:33.760 --> 00:44:35.680
I bring that kit everywhere.

00:44:35.760 --> 00:44:36.840
You know, Kongkwan,

00:44:36.920 --> 00:44:39.480
she'd always tear her clothes
or lose a button.

00:44:44.040 --> 00:44:45.040
Are you ready?

00:44:45.560 --> 00:44:47.480
- Yes.
- Let's go.

00:44:50.360 --> 00:44:51.640
Thank you.

00:45:01.840 --> 00:45:02.960
Mook.

00:45:03.040 --> 00:45:04.120
Is our food here?

00:45:09.320 --> 00:45:11.560
Mook, I can explain.

00:45:12.720 --> 00:45:14.240
No need to explain, Kuk.

00:45:14.760 --> 00:45:16.400
I don't think she's so stupid

00:45:16.480 --> 00:45:18.760
that she wouldn't know
what we're doing here.

00:45:20.280 --> 00:45:22.560
Why don't you vent out your frustration

00:45:22.640 --> 00:45:23.920
so she can hear you?

00:45:29.240 --> 00:45:31.280
Mook, please calm down.

00:45:32.560 --> 00:45:35.920
What else is there to explain?

00:45:36.000 --> 00:45:38.760
- Mook, it's not what it looks like!
- Back off!

00:45:38.840 --> 00:45:39.840
- Mook!
- Get back!

00:45:39.920 --> 00:45:41.440
Mook, Mook!

00:45:42.320 --> 00:45:43.360
Kuk!

00:45:44.400 --> 00:45:45.240
Sit down.

00:45:46.960 --> 00:45:48.880
See, this is why he's tired of you!

00:45:49.480 --> 00:45:51.240
Always so moody and bossy.

00:45:51.320 --> 00:45:52.480
No respect for your husband.

00:45:52.560 --> 00:45:53.840
Always on a power trip.

00:45:54.480 --> 00:45:57.360
No man can stand a woman like you!

00:45:59.960 --> 00:46:02.200
- Mook…
- It's over between us.

00:46:02.280 --> 00:46:03.760
Mook!

00:46:03.840 --> 00:46:05.440
Kuk, it's fine. Just stay here.

00:46:14.880 --> 00:46:16.040
Are you okay, Mook?

00:46:18.040 --> 00:46:18.880
Yes.

00:46:22.960 --> 00:46:23.800
{\an8}Hi, Mook.

00:46:24.720 --> 00:46:26.120
{\an8}It's been a while.

00:46:26.920 --> 00:46:27.760
{\an8}If I could choose,

00:46:28.800 --> 00:46:30.960
{\an8}I wouldn't want to see you
for the rest of my life.

00:46:31.040 --> 00:46:34.240
{\an8}Come on, Mook. Don't act like a child.

00:46:35.160 --> 00:46:37.280
{\an8}We're here as business rivals today.

00:46:37.880 --> 00:46:40.480
{\an8}Don't mix your work
with your personal life.

00:46:56.480 --> 00:46:58.080
Is something the matter?

00:46:58.160 --> 00:47:00.560
{\an8}It's nothing. We were just saying hello.

00:47:05.560 --> 00:47:08.480
Good afternoon. I'm Pitak Techanon.

00:47:08.560 --> 00:47:11.000
As a representative of TJ Group,

00:47:11.800 --> 00:47:15.360
I'd like to welcome you and thank you all

00:47:16.200 --> 00:47:18.960
{\an8}for your interest
in our project, You Are The One.

00:47:19.480 --> 00:47:21.280
Without further ado,

00:47:21.360 --> 00:47:23.320
I'd like to introduce you all

00:47:23.400 --> 00:47:27.040
{\an8}to Mr. Theechuda Teerasu,

00:47:27.120 --> 00:47:29.880
{\an8}a key executive at TJ Group.

00:47:50.120 --> 00:47:52.280
{\an8}Again, I'd like to officially welcome you

00:47:52.360 --> 00:47:56.600
and thank you all
for your interest in this pitch contest.

00:47:57.520 --> 00:48:00.920
I'm truly looking forward
to working with your companies.

00:48:02.800 --> 00:48:04.560
We will send you the task

00:48:05.280 --> 00:48:08.880
for the contest to select
our new partner company.

00:48:09.880 --> 00:48:12.120
{\an8}Every company will get the same task.

00:48:13.040 --> 00:48:16.080
You can find our company's information
in the envelopes provided.

00:48:18.880 --> 00:48:21.760
I'm looking forward to working
with your professional teams.

00:48:37.320 --> 00:48:39.640
{\an8}As for the selected company,

00:48:40.280 --> 00:48:42.120
we'll meet again to sign a contract.

00:48:43.120 --> 00:48:44.280
Thank you.

00:48:54.680 --> 00:48:57.200
{\an8}Are you okay? You're acting strange.

00:49:03.440 --> 00:49:05.160
I want to just curl up and die, Boss.

00:49:10.440 --> 00:49:12.440
I need to go take care of something.

00:49:12.520 --> 00:49:13.840
Let's meet back at the office.

00:49:42.000 --> 00:49:43.160
Hold on!

00:49:47.800 --> 00:49:49.520
Sorry! Sorry!

00:49:49.600 --> 00:49:51.120
I'm so sorry.

00:49:51.200 --> 00:49:54.080
- It's okay.
- Sorry.

00:49:54.680 --> 00:49:56.080
Mr. Thee.

00:49:56.840 --> 00:49:57.680
Are you okay, ma'am?

00:49:58.800 --> 00:50:00.400
I'm alright.

00:50:00.480 --> 00:50:02.320
I just wanted to talk to Mr. Thee.

00:50:02.400 --> 00:50:04.320
- I think--
- It's fine, Mr. Pitak.

00:50:12.840 --> 00:50:15.120
May I have five minutes of your time?

00:50:18.080 --> 00:50:20.440
I think you'd better deal
with your situation first.

00:50:26.120 --> 00:50:27.880
I know you remember me.

00:50:29.600 --> 00:50:31.520
Mr. Pitak, please take care of her.

00:50:38.160 --> 00:50:39.680
Why don't we talk later?

00:50:39.760 --> 00:50:41.040
Can you give me 15 minutes?

00:50:41.120 --> 00:50:42.760
I'd like to talk to Mr. Thee after that.

00:50:55.320 --> 00:50:56.600
Hello.

00:51:19.480 --> 00:51:20.640
Ms. Veluree's here, sir.

00:51:26.600 --> 00:51:27.680
Come on in.

00:51:41.760 --> 00:51:42.760
How can I help you?

00:51:45.400 --> 00:51:46.480
Well…

00:51:48.120 --> 00:51:51.440
I wanted to apologize
and ask for your forgiveness.

00:51:52.840 --> 00:51:55.560
I wasn't myself that night,
so it happened.

00:51:55.640 --> 00:51:58.200
And I didn't mean for it to happen.

00:51:59.960 --> 00:52:01.800
I hope it wouldn't affect

00:52:01.880 --> 00:52:04.360
your decision on who wins
The One's project.

00:52:06.360 --> 00:52:08.800
I don't mix work with nonsense.

00:52:10.600 --> 00:52:12.320
Is that all?

00:52:14.920 --> 00:52:15.880
Yes.

00:52:19.160 --> 00:52:20.920
May I suggest you one thing?

00:52:22.040 --> 00:52:25.800
If you and your boss
want to do something strange,

00:52:27.120 --> 00:52:28.640
please just get a room.

00:52:29.680 --> 00:52:31.720
Don't use the men's restroom at my hotel.

00:52:32.440 --> 00:52:34.040
It'll disturb the others.

00:52:37.440 --> 00:52:38.560
I'm almost there.

00:52:38.640 --> 00:52:40.040
Just a bit more.

00:52:43.920 --> 00:52:45.160
I was just mending his pants.

00:52:45.680 --> 00:52:47.200
Do I need a room for that?

00:52:49.880 --> 00:52:51.000
It'd be better, yes.

00:52:55.520 --> 00:52:57.520
If there’s nothing else,
you’re free to go.

00:52:59.000 --> 00:52:59.880
Alright.

00:53:03.320 --> 00:53:04.360
Oh,

00:53:04.920 --> 00:53:06.160
I just wanted to say,

00:53:07.040 --> 00:53:08.400
you should've worn that before.

00:53:09.280 --> 00:53:11.880
I think it suits you.

00:53:46.320 --> 00:53:50.160
Are you done? I'm starting to get dizzy.

00:54:04.280 --> 00:54:07.080
"The task for the travel agency
pitch contest

00:54:07.160 --> 00:54:10.000
to win a partnership with The One Hotel

00:54:10.080 --> 00:54:12.560
{\an8}in the You Are The One project is…"

00:54:13.080 --> 00:54:15.320
So, what is it, Mr. Pat?

00:54:19.240 --> 00:54:20.320
My apologies.

00:54:20.400 --> 00:54:21.720
Please continue, Mr. Pat.

00:54:23.960 --> 00:54:27.320
"Deliver a domestic tour program

00:54:27.400 --> 00:54:29.560
that you think is best for your pitch."

00:54:31.360 --> 00:54:33.880
Whan, go book a restaurant in advance
for our celebration.

00:54:33.960 --> 00:54:36.480
With an easy task like this,
we have it in the bag!

00:54:38.000 --> 00:54:39.200
But wait,

00:54:39.280 --> 00:54:41.640
why does the task seem so simple?

00:54:41.720 --> 00:54:44.880
This will decide which company
gets to partner with The One.

00:54:46.600 --> 00:54:48.040
Excuse me, Boss.

00:54:49.440 --> 00:54:50.280
Excuse me.

00:54:50.360 --> 00:54:51.800
I'm so excited.

00:54:54.920 --> 00:54:57.800
"Present the tour program
by the end of this week,

00:54:57.880 --> 00:54:59.560
then we will contact you

00:54:59.640 --> 00:55:01.640
to arrange a date and time
for an actual tour

00:55:01.720 --> 00:55:04.320
to test your program and service,

00:55:04.400 --> 00:55:06.520
{\an8}which will affect the final decision.

00:55:06.600 --> 00:55:09.360
The judge is Mr. Thee,
an executive at The One."

00:55:10.480 --> 00:55:12.200
This task was made for us!

00:55:12.280 --> 00:55:13.920
I swear we'll win this for sure.

00:55:14.000 --> 00:55:15.720
- Yeah!
- I trust your skills, Mook.

00:55:15.800 --> 00:55:18.040
They won't turn us down for sure.

00:55:19.840 --> 00:55:23.240
Guys, I want information
on the popular travel spots

00:55:23.320 --> 00:55:26.440
- Write it down!
- trending online in every province.

00:55:26.960 --> 00:55:29.040
Bonus points if it's super new.

00:55:29.120 --> 00:55:31.560
I'm going to plan a new program
no one's done before.

00:55:31.640 --> 00:55:34.320
- You got it!
- You got it!

00:55:35.000 --> 00:55:36.440
Can you do that in an hour?

00:55:36.520 --> 00:55:37.480
‪An hour?!

00:55:37.560 --> 00:55:39.120
- Go, go!
- Go!

00:55:39.200 --> 00:55:40.480
- Let's go.
- We got this!

00:55:40.560 --> 00:55:41.600
Let's go!

00:55:41.680 --> 00:55:44.200
- Come on, let's go!
- Mook…

00:55:44.280 --> 00:55:45.080
Yes?

00:55:45.160 --> 00:55:46.160
Where'd you go?

00:55:46.240 --> 00:55:47.280
Why are your clothes all dirty?

00:55:47.880 --> 00:55:49.680
It's a long story, Boss.
I'll tell you later.

00:55:49.760 --> 00:55:51.320
I'd better go do my work. Bye.

00:56:22.440 --> 00:56:23.800
Oh, Kuk.

00:56:25.320 --> 00:56:27.280
How was the briefing?

00:56:27.360 --> 00:56:29.200
Do we have a shot?

00:56:32.960 --> 00:56:34.840
I don't know yet, Ma.

00:56:34.920 --> 00:56:37.000
We still have to send them our program.

00:56:38.400 --> 00:56:43.120
But there's only one company
that seems to stand a chance against us.

00:56:43.800 --> 00:56:45.880
Mook's husband's company, right?

00:56:47.640 --> 00:56:49.160
{\an8}What a coincidence.

00:56:49.240 --> 00:56:51.640
{\an8}Speak of the devil, and he appears.

00:56:52.240 --> 00:56:53.960
{\an8}- Who are you calling the devil?
- Usa…

00:56:54.480 --> 00:56:55.480
{\an8}Go ahead, then.

00:56:56.000 --> 00:56:58.720
{\an8}You hit me, I hit you back. Fair game.

00:57:01.160 --> 00:57:03.440
{\an8}Oh? Mr. Thee! Wait.

00:57:05.640 --> 00:57:07.240
{\an8}This angle's perfect.

00:57:07.320 --> 00:57:08.600
{\an8}Let me take a picture for you.

00:57:08.680 --> 00:57:11.080
{\an8}One, two, three--

00:57:22.720 --> 00:57:23.920
{\an8}Right there, please.

00:58:19.720 --> 00:58:22.000
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya